wadi musa , ( , literally ‘ valley of moses ’ ) , is the name of a town located in the ma'an governorate in southern jordan east of petra at latitude 30.317n and longitude 35.483e.   it is the nearest town to the archaeological site of petra and hosts many hotels and restaurants for tourists visiting this place .

petra : ( alex presents the clue from petra , jordan . )   petra is built on a terrace overlooking wadi musa the valley of this man , who tradition says struck a rock here & made it gush with water

